ACP fairs have been held from 2002 to 2008 to promote ACP products. From 2002 to 2006, the fairs remained fixed to the dates of the summits while from 2007 onwards, fairs are held on the same dates as the ACP Leaders week. Some of the major countries which the fact-missions had visited to showcase ACP products were Guinea Bissau, Niger, Cape Verde, and Fiji. Countries such as Congo B., U.K., India and the EU have also participated during the ACP fairs to give exposure to the ACP regions and promote ACP products. Presently, the ACSG Fair Promotion Programme is being administered by the African Private Enterprise Foundation (APEF).
